name: Graph-Format
content:
c It's easy to create your own graph using the format described below.
c You can download it to your computer, give the file a name,
c then upload it again.
c Or you can use a text editor to create a graph on your computer
c and upload it.

c Lines beginning with 'c' are ignored.

c A line beginning with 'n' creates a node; the format is
c   n ID X Y [WEIGHT]
c where ID is a unique identifier, usually a number,
c X and Y are x- and y-coordinates, and WEIGHT is an optional weight
n 1 20 20 35
n 2 30 20
n 3 20 35 4
n 4 25 40

c A line beginning with 'e' creates an edges; the format is
c   e SOURCE TARGET [WEIGHT]
c where SOURCE and TARGET are the two endpoints of the edge;
c if the graph is directed, the arrowhead is at TARGET
e 1 2 7
e 1 3 13
e 2 4
e 4 2 5
c There can be two edges with the same endpoints
c  if they go in opposite directions.

c Nodes and edges can have other attributes,
c  such as color, shape (nodes), or width (edges)
c The format for these is
c   ATTRIBUTE:VALUE
n 5 40 20 color:blue shape:star
n 6 40 30 11 shape:square

e 5 6 color:red width:7
e 6 2 17 color:green
